  "lede": "Look, I've seen enough itineraries that promise a 'charming Southern escape' and deliver nothing but overpriced fluff and endless packing. That's not what we're doing here. This is the real deal: a practical, no-bullshit roadmap to experiencing the lower Mississippi River corridor, with Natchez, Mississippi, as your home base. Why Natchez? Because it's perfectly situated, steeped in history, and frankly, the Big Muddy Inn knows how to treat you right without all the unnecessary pomp. We're talking about two substantial 'return trips' – out to the raw, visceral heart of the Delta and down to the vibrant, chaotic soul of New Orleans – all while minimizing the hassle of checking in and out of hotels every single night. I'll tell you what's worth the drive, what's worth the detour, and what you can skip without a second thought. Get ready to roll down the windows and let the South seep in.",
