      "heading": "Day 4: Natchez – Your Well-Deserved Rest Day",
      "paragraphs": [
        "<p>After the intensity of the Delta, today is all about Natchez. Sleep in. Enjoy a proper, leisurely breakfast. The beauty of having Natchez as your hub is that you get these decompression days. No driving schedules, no check-ins. Today, you can truly soak in the charm of this historic town. For lunch, try <b>Maison Blanche</b> on Main Street for a delightful, fresh menu in a beautiful setting, or grab a sandwich from <a href=\"https://www.natchezmarket.com/\">Natchez Market</a> and find a bench overlooking the river.</p><p>This is the day to dive into Natchez’s famous antebellum homes. <a href=\"https://www.stantonhall.com/\">Stanton Hall</a> is a grand, opulent mansion that offers a fantastic guided tour, giving you a real sense of the pre-Civil War wealth and lifestyle. Then, head to <a href=\"https://www.natchezgardenclub.org/melrose/\">Melrose</a> (part of Natchez National Historical Park), which provides a more nuanced look at both the owners and the enslaved people who built and maintained these estates. Don’t feel obliged to tour every single house; pick two that appeal to you. Skip the ones that feel too much like a stage show; focus on those that offer genuine historical insights. Afterwards, browse the shops downtown – there are some lovely antique stores and local boutiques. As the sun begins to dip, make your way back to the Natchez Bluff. Grab a drink from a nearby establishment and find your spot. Watching the sun set over the Mississippi River, painting the sky in fiery hues, is a Natchez ritual, and it’s genuinely unforgettable. For dinner, consider <a href=\"https://www.magnoliabloom.com/\">Magnolia Bluffs Casino Hotel</a> for a more modern dining experience, or stick to the local favorites you’ve discovered. Just relax and recharge; tomorrow, we’re heading south to New Orleans.</p>"
      ]
    },
